        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 7:30AM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 730 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 8 miles south of Colstrip to near Lame
Deer, or extending from 8 miles south of Colstrip to 22 miles south
of Colstrip, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lame Deer, Ashland, Birney Village, Muddy Cluster, Brandenberg and
Northern Cheyenne Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
